deck_excerpt: An Extra Deck Eldlich list that utilizes Level 2, Level/Rank 5, and Level 8 Synchro and Xyz monsters
deck_description: Hi, Grayewick here. He who likes the summoning of monsters through Fusion. Back with another Eldlich deck profile but this time, it's not necessarily budget but a more concentrated one. Extra Deck Eldlich, to be more specific. Before anything else, I wanna make it clear that this is NOT the stun variant of Eldlich that runs three copies of Skill Drain, but instead a more reactive and interactive Extra Deck variant so if you're looking for the latter, this is not that type of deck. The non-standard stuff: • x3 Solemn Judgment - Despite what the category states, three of this one is absolutely mandatory, including your one copy of Golden Land Forever!. I can never stress this enough, you NEED protection against Evenly Matched. Lightning Storm is just, whatever. • x3 Evenly Matched - Not only do you need protection against it, you also need it in case your opponent decides to make you go second. Arguably the best board wipe in the game, even better than the overrated Lightning Storm that's a UR, btw. • x3 Heavy Storm Duster - You need interaction against back row, in addition to your Evenly Matched. You can't rely on just one form of removal. This can also save your Golden Land and Eldlixir traps from Evenly Matched by chaining it and destroying those. • x3 Ice Dragon's Prison - The second best form of removal in the game. It does not target, it does not destroy, and it's banishing is optional. • x3 Lost Wind - This card, alongside Psy-Framelord Omega is just pure cheat code. It's basically a Phantom Knights' Fog Blade or Infinite Impermanence, but better. You can use it as a discard fodder for your Paleozoic Dinomischus, and it'll just reset itself on to the field as soon as your opponent Special Summons an Extra Deck monster. • x3 Paleozoic Dinomischus - Better than Raigeki Break or even Karma Cut. It does not discard for cost, it's a generic face-up banishing removal, it can also be a body on board. It's wonderful. Also a body on board for purposes that we'll address later. • x1 Psy-Framelord Omega - The second boss monster of the deck. This deck is the reason why you'll never run out of Lost Wind and Paleozoic Dinomischus because during your opponent's Standby Phases, you can return a banished copy of them back to the graveyard. That's insane. You can also just pitch this card to the graveyard for your Dogmatika Punishment and it can recycle back one of the cards in the graveyard, including itself, and this is not a once per turn effect. • x1 Shiranui Shogunsaga - Just a beat stick in case you locked yourself out of attacking with the Cursed Eldland. And he's free. • x1 Draco Berserker of the Tenyi - An even bigger beat stick that can interrupt your opponent by not necessarily negating the effects of your opponent's monsters, but banishes them. • x1 Colossal Fighter - This spot is absolutely free. I only chose this because it's a monster that keeps coming back and isn't a once per turn. • x1 Armades, Keeper of Boundaries, Adreus, Keeper of Armageddon, and Ally of Justice Catastor - Armades makes landing game ending attacks easier, Catastor gets rid of problematic non-DARK monsters without targeting, and Adreus is a generic spot removal and holds your Golden Land monsters as well to slow down the tempo of the game. You don't want Eldlich to speed through your in-archetype Traps. Any of their slots can be flex spots. • x1 Crimson Knight Vampire Bram - This card is funny. He's a Zombie type monster, which means Cursed Eldland won't lock you out of attacking with him, he has 2500 ATK which is pretty sizeable. He can steal monsters from your opponent's graveyard, and if your opponent for some reason happens to have some Divine Arsenal AA-Zeus - Sky Thunder or any boss monster just chillin' in there like Blue-Eyes Chaos MAX Dragon for example, you can just yoink it. He also brings himself back during the next Standby Phases after the turn he was destroyed, and all it takes to make him is your Conquistador and Huaquero, which shouldn't be difficult. • x1 Number 45: Crumble Logos the Prophet of Demolition - He's technically a floodgate, and is a pretty sizeable beat stick at 2200 ATK (can crash with El Shaddoll Winda, pog), and most importantly, he's a Zombie type monster. • x1 Sky Cavalry Centaurea - If this card is good enough to out Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon or Destiny HERO - Destroyer Phoenix Enforcer, it's good enough for decks that can make it that does not have those incredible boss monsters. This monster is the main reason why I'm running Paleozoic Olenoides and Paleozoic Canadia. • x3 Paleozoic Marella - This card is just free Eldlich set up. It dumps a trap card from your deck to the GY. ANY trap card. Also a free body for your Synchro and Xyz plays. Everything else should be pretty obvious. I mean, it's Eldlich. You can cut cards that you don't like or don't have access to yet. Nothing much else to say about it. Enjoy climbing.

deck_excerpt: My current 2022 Eldlich build with some thoughts written in the description on the state of the deck.
deck_description: This is my current updated build of Trap Eldlich for February 2022, at this point I'm 99% comfortable and happy with the list even accounting for a potential Imperial Order ban. By no means do I believe Eldlich is a dead deck despite potentially losing a power 1-of, I think for a returning player or someone wanting to go from being "casual" to having a "locals" or potentially higher in certain metas level deck, this is an extremely safe deck to play, learn and get used to the game.  While not being Extra Deck reliant, you still definitely have the opportunity to access some real haymakers such as Zeus or Ningirsu and the sheer advantage engine granted by the natural progression of the game through using stuff like your Eldlixir of Scarlet Sanguine and Conquistador's graveyard effects really keep you going strong without a great deal of worry. However, one must take time with all decks like this to learn when to use their resources and maintain that advantage engine to avoid burning themselves out at the crucial moments of the game.  Edit: It appears Eldlich got even better than before.

deck_excerpt: I've tried to adapt my TCG list into Master Duels. Currently Plat II with 52 wins and 10 losses.
deck_description:
I've tried to adapt my TCG list into Master Duels. By only playing this deck, I've reached Plat II with 52 wins and 10 losses. One thing that I really dislike is the fact that it seems like you have to play Maxx C in this format. Without it you will have a rough time playing against all the combo decks. I think its also mandatory to play 3x Ash and 2x Called By because of the fact that your opponent could have his own Maxx C in his hand. My thought process building this deck was to make the deck as consistent as it can be in the BO1 format with a ban list that has Nadir Servant at 1 and Magical Meltdown at 2. This is why I use 3x Pot of Prosperity with only 5 Shaddoll Monsters. You really dont want them to brick you because it can be a really hard game if you start with 2-3 Shaddols in your hand. Also I've cut out the one copy of Ariel because it hasn't seen much use besides being a normal summon to go into Almiraj to get your Maximus going. The extra deck has some choices that I'm still testing.
  1. First things first. I would never cut the 2nd Mechaba or Winda. You will need 2 Mechabas in a lot of duels while having 2 Windas helps you to combo with your 1st Winda to go into your 2nd one on the next turn using Shaddoll Schism.
  2. Yes I am playing the one copy of Magellanica as a huge Beatstick can be enough to ruin your enemys day in Master Duels. Also it's a good target for Super Polymerization against decks like Tri Brigade. It can also be used with the enemys Maxx C from the grave so you can make this guy really often.
  3. Starvin Venom Fusion Dragon can come in clutch but wont come out in the most duels.
  4. Cards that you could cut from the extra deck in my opinion: Pugatrio, Raidjin, Starvin Venom Fusion Dragon, Magellanica
  5. Cards that you could add to the extra deck in my opinion: 2nd Apkallone, 2nd N'tss, Mudragon of the Swamp
There are still a lot of possibilitys on how you can adapt the deck.
  1. Play 2x Dogmatika Maximus becuase Nadir Servant is at 1
  2. Cut out one Shaddoll Fusion because the Shaddoll package is really small und play a lot vs stuff like Eldlich
  3. Put in something like Harpyies Feather Duster or LS to have an easier time vs Eldlich, etc. (I think the deck still perfoms really good against Eldlich without those but it will help in the matchup)
  4. Use Nibiru instead of Maxx C for another Light monster to go into Mechaba or Construct

deck_excerpt: To celebrate reaching Platinum 1, I'm sharing the deck that I used to achieved the rank! An incredible anti-meta rogue deck, Generaider Windwitch slow
deck_description: I achieved Platinum 1 rank with Generaider Windwitch 01/24/2022 with a 70%-ish winrate, consistently taking down decks like Shadoll-Invoked, Sky Striker, Tribrigade and Adamancipators! If you want a detailed explanation how to use this deck, click here. This deck features incredibly potent anti-meta cards like Dimension Shifter, Macro Cosmos, Imperial Order and True King of Calamities. Generaider Windwitch plays comfortably under these floodgates, while the opponent keels over and dies. If you have access to any of these cards, they generally insta-win you the game since they shut off almost every route of play. While preferring to go first, this deck can still comfortably go second if forced to, since it features 12 hand traps. It can also play past interruption, since it has multiple methods to start off its gameplay. I found it funny that almost nobody knows what the heck Generaiders and Windwitches do, and they end up underestimating the deck until it's too late. Before long, your opponent may find themself facing down Harr's omni-negate, Crystal Wing's monster negate, Dimension Shifter's banish, and lethal backrow like Judgment and Imperial Order! Another bonus about this deck is that it functions nicely under Maxx "C," the undisputed king of Master Duel. This deck doesn't summon much, so the opponent doesn't have much incentive to use Maxx "C." This deck can even function under Summon Limit or Winda! The only major problem about this deck is that it bricks HARD, since there are 6 "hard" bricks in the deck (5 Generaider bosses + Ice Bell) and 1 "soft" brick (Glass Bell). This weakness is avoided with Pot of Prosperity and Maxx "C" functioning as cards that will get you starters for the deck. If you ever use this deck in Master Duel, I hope you enjoy piloting it as much as I do!

deck_excerpt: A well rounded Superheavy deck build
deck_description: Just my personal Superheavy setup. Main strategy revolves around utilizing Soulpiercer to draw the cards you need to summon Benkei (Flutist if Benkei is in hand, Peacemaker if not). Also using battleball to tribute opponent's monster for your synchros, especially any of their level 10's to summon Steamtrain. Brute force your way to a win with big damage by utilizing Horns and/or Soulshield on Benkei or any high level synchro. This can be particularly effective with Stealth Ninja's direct attack. Never be quick to surrender with this deck, if i've learned anything using it in 100's of duels, it's the amount of surprising comeback victories it can achieve, don't be afraid to grind things out, one card can make all the difference.   Key points: . Gigagloves, Brawler and Swordsman make for great stall tactics. . Get your Gigagloves, Flutists and Soulpiercers into the GY ASAP for their effects. . Waraji and Transporter can always be special summoned at any time during main phases, combine this with Trumpeter's special summon or Fist's GY effect for quick synchro summons. Magnet can be also be useful here as your normal summon, depending on your hand. . Use Peacemaker tribute effect on Gigagloves, Flutist or Soulpiercer preferably. . Save your equip cards for Benkei or synchros. . Shutendoji is essential for going second and wiping out your opponent's backrow or field spells. . Stealth Ninja can direct attack, make use of this to divert flip effects or effects that occur when opponent's monster is battled. . Sarutobi and Thief can be used in a pinch to destroy opponent's spells/traps, should Shutendoji fail. . Thief and Susanowo can steal opponent's spells/traps from field/graveyard for your own use, or simply to prevent the opponent from using them or activating their effects in the GY. . Musashi is generally used only in a combo to retrieve the quick special summon cards from your graveyard (Waraji, Trumpeter etc)  to summon higher level synchros, don't use him for battle unless you need to. . Flutist can summon Benkei directly from your hand. Peacemaker can summon Benkei from your deck by attaching to and tributing any of your monsters. Waraji can be used as '2 tributes' to summon Benkei. . Whenever you have a chance to summon Steamtrain, do so. . Protect your high level monsters from battle or card effect destruction with Soulbeads and Soulfire Suit. . Remember that Stealth Ninja revives itself from the GY at the start of your turn if it was destroyed by card effect, save cards in your hand for a comeback if you expect this. . Drum can be used as an offbeat tuner, or to revive a fallen boss monster. . Scarecrow can be used for an emergency revival of a boss monster, as well as potentially get a Flutist or Gigagloves in your GY simultaneously.    Key weaknesses: . Skill Drain, Forbidden Chalice, or any effect negation . Effects which alter battle position and/or prevent position from being altered (Enemy Controller, etc) . Effects that target defense position monsters (Dark Mirror Force, Ehren Lightsworn Monk, Red Dragon Archfiend, Number 21 etc) . Mystic Mine can shut this deck down completely.

deck_excerpt: 100% Consistent. That's the idea of the wins you'll get. Ez GG's. Since every card in your deck SS to board +1 plus GY recursion.
deck_description:
420 CP UR* 300 CP SR 330 CP R 450 CP N DECK STATS ATTACK 7 DEFENSE 10* CONSISTENCY 10* VERSATILITY 7 RECOVERY 9* MORE STATS DRAW POWER 4/5* CONTROL 3/5 BURN 0/5 OTK/FTK 4/5* STAMINA 2/5 COUNTER 4/5* SWARM 5/5* Stats with * next em' indicate Strengths. CP from SideDeck don't count since MasterDuel has no SideDeck. It's there for you to know what you could add to the base deck to counter anything in current or future meta that may pose problem with this decklist. Mass Swarm field on turn 1 or 2 with full board (if you feel safe *have 1 or 2 ways to recover Borrelsword from GY if opponent Board Wipes or stop at 4 summons) of Fur Hire in this order of importance.
  1. Beat
  2. Seal
  3. Recon
  4. Filo
  5. Donpa
  6. Helmer
  7. Bravo
When you get to 4 Fur Hires SS I:P Masquerena using 2 Fur Hires then SS Borrelsword Dragon onto board using I:P Masquerena and 1 more Fur Hire and Win game most of the time. It's very hard for opponent to deal with 1 or 2 Borrelswords that dont get destroyed by effects or battle. Hence, Immortal FurHire! We dont counter Ash Blossom or Effect Veiler there's ways to do that but it's not worth putting in deck to counter Ash Blossom or Veiler. Less consistent if we add cards to counter it. Added 3 copies of I:P Masquerena so you can protect all 3 copies of your Borrelsword Dragon (You need that for clever opponents) from Effects so it won't be destroyed by both Card Effects and Battle. Masquerena also allows you to point a link so you can use World Legacy Succession to SS Borrelsword from GY in case it does get wiped somehow. Added protection. Added 3 copies of Maxx 'C' because every deck in rank is SS turn 1 or 2. This draws you lots of cards if its in your opening hand. Updated - Now has a ton more GY recursion + More Summons up to 26 for consistency. There's too much control decks floating around with tons of Board Wipes you need to be able to recover your Borrelsword from GY if this happens or you loose 4 summons. 100% Consistent. That's the idea of the wins you'll get. Ez GG's. Since every card in your deck SS to board +1 plus GY recursion.

deck_name: My Paleozoic Frog Deck POST banlist  2022 (FEB)
deck_excerpt: does this count as a project of science?
deck_description: Since I was little I have been fascinated with natural history, wondering how such bizarres creatures lived  on Earth. This and other things have became a passionate hobby to me so in this context the  Paleozoic Frog deck appears to me the most. The Paleozoic cards are almost an ideal representation of  animals that once lived on Earth( in the  Cambrian Period), so well detailed  which got me in love. So enough about boring stuff and let's get into the deck.   One to rules them All The paleozoic  Frog  is a strategy  based in a control type of deck using traps ( and occasionally handtraps) as the main resource of such action. The majority of Paleozoic archetype are trap cards  with a variety of effects, while having a gimmick to summon themself as a monster (AQUA levEl 2 , 1200 ATK/ 0 DEF) in a CL1 with a trap. Frogs are level 2 AQUA monster which have the ability to swarm the field fast as they can, while aiming to go for the big guy of their archetype Toadally Awesome (what a goof name), a Rank 2 aqua monster with a totally awesome omni negate effect. Both engines were born to be together, they are so complementary for each other that makes a fearsome rogue strategy. Who is who on Cruj (a silly brazilian joke) Frogs everywhere 3x Swap Frog: Our silly boy , swap frog is the heart and soul for the frog engine. First of all , the first effect ( a frog's  Foolish burial when it's summoned) is not  once per turn, so you can bounce itself for an additional Gy set up,  like  a Ronintoadin and a  Dupe frog. You can even use the Toadally Awesome effect to summon Swap frog from the deck  to extend your play to go in a second Toadally Awesome. 3x Dupe frog: A control's  graduated, this cute little frog is our food for Swap frog and  Ronintoadin  to work well. It has a second major effect  to add a frog monster to your hand from deck which is good also because you can use it to go in a link monster  (Marincess Coral Anemone or Mista boy) 2x Ronintoadin : This wanna-be samurai can be summoned from your  Gy banning  a  frog card and that's not a once per turn effect. The swarm ability  of this card is incredible. 3x Toadally Awesome: A XYZ monster with so much power. These little bastards can detach  a material to summon a frog from the deck , tribute an Aqua monster to negate ANY effect and  if  they go to Gy , can recover a  water monster( itself or another frog). The scariest part is that none of these effects are "hard" once per turn ( in other word, if you have more than one on field you can use  this effect again), making this card a fearsome entity. If  you have(as I have) Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder, this card becomes  even scarier.   Honorary Frogs 2x Marincess Coral Anemone: An Idol makes an appearance in this deck. She is a brilliant extender, you can  use  Swap frog to send Dupe frog to GY , bounce itself to send a Ronintoadin  to Gy, use the Ronintoadin to summon it  and go into  Marincess Coral Anemone summon again Swap frog from Gy. using another time it effects sending another  dupe frog to bring Ronintoadin once more to go into Toadally Awesome... phew... Marincess Coral Anemone is insane... 1x Mista boy: one of the elemental links , it can boost Toadally Awesome and if goes to gy , recover any water monster. 1x Cat Shark : A rank 2 XYZ cute fellow can boost even more the atk of Toadally Awesome.   Cambrian period 2x Paleozoic Pikaia : Pikaia  is an extinct, primitive  animal known from the Middle Cambrian that looks like an Eel. Our Pikaia sent a paleozoic card from hand to GY for draw 2 new cards. Can help to set up your GY  and renovate your hand and (of course) create a CL1 to summon any Paleozoic trap card from your Gy 3x Paleozoic Canadia: Canadia (meaning of Canada or after Canada) is a genus of extinct primitive annelid worms similar to modern  marine annelid worms. Our  Canadia is a Book of  moon in a trap card form, flipping any non link monster as you like  to stop our disturb any link, synchro ou XYZ plays. This is not as impactful as a  Solemn Strike,however it breaks the  tempo of your opponent and this is the most important thing. 3x Paleozoic Dinomischus : Dinomischus is a rare fossil animal from the Cambrian period, looking like an  actinia or  a Jellyfish offspring. Our Dinomischus is an insane card that can banish any face-up card of the field and, like  Pikaia,  can set the Gy with any card. Removing from play an  Eldlich or a Zoo is what makes this deck scary. 3x Paleozoic Olenoides:Olenoides was a trilobite(Trilobites  means "three lobes" are a group of extinct marine artiopodan arthropods, looking like Woodlouse) from the Cambrian period. Our Olenoides will destroy any spell/trap card on field. No flood gates like mystic mine or  There can be only one, just perfect 2x Paleozoic Opabinia:Opabinia regalis is an extinct, stem group arthropod found in the Middle Cambrian ,was a soft-bodied animal, averaging about 5. 7 cm in length (excluding proboscis), and its segmented body had lobes along the sides and a fan-shaped tail, looking like a alien crab or a giant shrimp. Our Opabinia, a XYZ monster, can add any paleozoic card  from deck to your hand and also makes any Paleozoic trap cards in hand Trap. A great control card. 1xPaleozoic Anomalocaris :Anomalocaris ("unlike other shrimp", or "abnormal shrimp") is an extinct genus of radiodont (anomalocaridid), an order of animals thought to be closely related to ancestral arthropods. Our Anomacaris, a  XYZ monster, is a occasionally  a beater and an extender that can dig even more into your deck every time that a trap card is active. Can also pop a card on the field if it has a trap card has a material.   Honorary Paleozoic 2x Trap trick: Traptrickus  is an extinct animal that.. HAHAHA, I'm kidding , this card is an amazing search for paleozoic cards as any other trap card in this deck.   Control tool box 3x Infinite Impermanence: an awesome card to stop any effect monster on the field, dan can even start your own play by triggering the effect of any paleozoic in the gy. 2x Anti-Spell Fragrance : Same as the difunct  imperial order, an awesome floodgate  to counter any spell card. 3x Lost wind:  Negate the effect of  a monster and half its atk and if your opponent goes into a Extra deck monster you can re-set this card of the field. Multi use trap card. 2x Gozen match: Effective against deck that use multiplus attributes like  Dragon link or Virtual world. 2x Solemn Judgment: Your  favorite "no no no" card 2x Crackdown: Steals any monster for you opponent and you can link of on  an I:P Mascarena,  Cerberus or just let them on  field helping you. 2x Get  Out!: An underestimate card which can kick out any 2 extra deck monsters  from the field, the  only downside is that your opponent has to  have 2 extra deck monsters at least one field. 2x Effect Veiler: Negates any monster effect. 3x Dimensional Barrier: A well rounded card to  help you stop any summon that nags  you, specially those annoying  birds monsters. The paleozoic time travels:   1x Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder: Cat shark and any paleozoic xyz loves it. You can make it in any moments to insure your victory over you adversary. 1x Borreload Dragon: My favorite beater  , but you can use any link 4 that you desire. 1x I:p Masquerena: My favorite troublemaker, seh can go into cerberus, Borreload or  Unicorn, granting her protection effect. 1x Knightmare Unicorn: Shuffles any cards on the opponent's field. Can be deadly if you use in the opponent's turn with  I:p Masquena effect. 1x Knightmare Cerberus:  Pops any monster. It can be really useful with Crackdown to get rid off   Side deck 3X Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring and  3 x Droll & Lock Bird: Prevents draws 3x Ghost Mourner & Moonlit Chill:  Helps you to win in a time call out. 2x Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion: No GY  for you; 1x  Dinowrestler Pankratops: pops any card that may or may not be useful. 3X Dark Ruler No More: no more oppressive boards by these vicious Drytron players      A natural history Frog Paleozoic aren't near the top strategy that was in the past  but, like all rogues deck, can put up a well balanced fight and can surprise any opponents if she/he doesn't take care. I hope you enjoy the deck, and you can have fun playing this deck as much as I .

deck_excerpt: I've missed this deck so much (also why the hell is skill drain at three, who thought that that was a good idea in any form)
deck_description: So for anyone who didn't play around 2019 format, this was a very strong rouge option with a really cool toolbox of cards. We just got a few of those off of the banlist that just came out (although I'm not a fan of the list overall). Destrudo allows for some synchro 7 plays like dawn dragster going first and black rose going second, and snow is really strong sense you should have a full graveyard at almost all times. Hydralander is one of the centerpieces of the deck, it's a big body that has a quick effect mill 3 and pop, the drawback being that you can't have any monsters with the same name in the graveyard, another reason snow is so good is that it can help manipulate the grave to get out duplicates of those cards. Over the past few banlists BA has also gotten some major unhits in the forms of three tour guide, cir, and graff. Sekka is a crazy draw spell that is pot of greed and upstart goblin in the same card, but with the major drawback of it being the only piece of backrow you can play for the game, it's at one right now so you won't find it always, but it's still very powerful. the dangers provide extra draw power and extension. Also remember that beatrice can mill destrudo or snow to get them into rotation quickly.

Swordsoul Snow (Jan 2022) Feb' Banlist

The new banlist made many players angry for getting hits at their favorite decks and made others happy for the same reason, but everyone have found a common enemy: Skill Drain. xD I ain't a long date Dragon Link player, to be more precise i started recently, and i really liked it. Like a whole lot. But its hard and just isn't getting any easier so far, so to make things more fluid for me i added a Halqifibrax combo that end with 2 negates and 1 floodgate.   2 card combo: Black Metal Dragon + any dragon extender. Normal summon Black Metal ~Link summon Striker Dragon using Black Metal ~Chain link 1 Black Metal and link 2 Striker, adding in sequence Boot Sector launch and Red-eyes Darkness Metal Dragon (if you have Noctovision Dragon in hand special summon it now) ~(if you didn't special summoned Noctovision but have Quick Launch in hand use it now[Boot sector can also be used as a extender]) Link summon Dragunity Knight - Romulus using Striker and the dragon extender, Romulus add Dragon Ravine (if you used Noctovision for the link summon you can chainblock) ~activate Dragon Ravine, trigger it effect to discard a card and send Destrudo the Lost Dragon's Frisson to the GY ~Romulus already did his job so special summon Darkness Metal by banishing him ~activate Darkness Metal effect to special a Dragon tuner from your graveyard ~take a breath ~link Summon Crystron Halqifibrax using Darkness Metal and the tuner ~Halqifibrax special summon Deskbot 001 from your deck or hand ~Link summon Mecha Phantom Beast Auroradon using you know what ~Auroradon will summon 3 tokens and after that summon 001 from your Graveyard ~synchro summon Cupid Pitch Using a token and 001 ~Activate Auroradon and tribute 2 tokens to special summon Mecha Phantom Beast Coltwing from your deck ~Coltwing will summon 2 tokens and after that summon 001 by the last time ~Synchro summon Borreload Savage Dragon using Cupid Pitch and a token ~Chain Savage and Cupid effects. Add Creation Resonator from your deck to your hand ~special summon said Resonator ~Synchro summon Baronne de Fleur using the Resonator and Coltwing* (Coltwing is now level 7 because there's only one token in the board) ~activate Destrudo in the Graveyard and Target Deskbot 001* (if you target the token you won't get Shenshen but Dawn Dragster) ~Synchro summon Shenshen using Destrudo and the token. The result isn't as impressive as it's long, but, to me, is easier to remember than pure dragon link ever-adapting combos. Although that you can play like a normal dragon link deck to some extent if you need to play around something like nibiru or if you draw Coltwing (Coltwing is the only Brick in this deck). I tested other extenders like Ready Fusion but i decided to preserve the extra deck as it is now. !Update: added a new line for the combo. Now instead of targeting Deskbot 001 with Destrudo you can target the Auroradon token and make Shooting Riser Dragon that will send Fairy Tail - Snow to the GY.   Sorry for any grammar mistakes. Any suggestions are welcome. GLHF

deck_excerpt: No one reads Yugioh Cards. Take advantage of it. Unga Bunga
deck_description:
Turtle turn 1 with bait/trickery.  Examples:
  • Yugioh Players don't read, so by NS Wento then activating Gactos, you'll get rid of their Maxx "C" because they think you're going into a weird combo. Just stop after summoning Gactos, they'll get a draw but you're likely to have Bashelios or a few S/T for protections.
  • Make your opponent think they should worry about a card like Meteoragon, so they'll focus on outing it by battle only for you to buff more with Wento
  • Another bait is to get your opponent to negate the wrong monster. Fortia and Orpis are the biggest offenders. Everyone knows that Fortia searches, but Orpis' effect to send Bashelios to the GY and then summon can win you a game by ATKing directly for 2900+
  • Activate Mountain first when you plan on crashing Fortia/Orpis for a search. If your opponent has an Ash, then they'll use it on Mountain because that the "Money Card" and if they don't then that means you get a free Meteoragon in the Battle Phase
  • Everyone expects Imperm to be in the middle, place it right of the middle
  • If you have 2 traps + Imperm, don't set Imperm. You don't want to risk Harpie'
Turn 2: UNGA BUNGA
  • When ATKing, remember to use your level 4/5's first THEN activate Skylar. She prevents you from ATKing with lv5 or lower monsters once activated
  • Yes. Meteoragon is not a hard OPT.
  • Yes. Meteoragon does negate a monster's ATK bonus like Accesscode
  • Yes. Meteoragon does negate "Cannot be destroyed by battle or Card effects"
  • 2x Magnum Shield + Bashelios = 8700 direct ATK
  • Save Bashelios to ATK last just in case
Final Remarks:
  • I'd play 3x Solemn Judgement but I just don't for 0 reason. You could replace the Magnum shield if you need to.
  • You can pop off heavily but there's a lot of times that you can just brick and stall
  • Keep track of your effects and read your opponents.

Rise to new Heights  Floowandereeze has gotten itself a reputation as a somewhat boring to play against and linear deck. But playing it, the deck offers a lot of variety. There are plenty of ways to either chainblock or dodge a handtrap. The order in which you summon your birds can be changed up to bait negates. All of that may not sound like the plays differ much from one another and they don't, but you do get a kick out of every first turn hand since the way you'll handle your turn and the decisions you make differ every time.  Journey Preparations (Advent of Adventure) gave this deck both a searcher and a way to play through interaction in one, banishing one to chainblock or chaining it to an Imperm to dogde it.  In current build people usually play 3 Book of Moon and Gold Sarcophagus but Advent achieves both while also boosting consistency.  Dimension Shifter is one heck of a handtrap and Floowandereeze can activate it multiple times as they usually keep their GY empty. Even if they don't, Stri can banish whatever's in there.  Also their design is fantastic. Not only the monsters themselves but the way the entire background is utilizes to create awesome card design is great. The floodgate effect of Empen is also not too strong and designed in a way in which a floodgate is acceptable.

Master Duel Users: They Semi-Limited Pot of Duality. Replace it with a Terraforming.

The strategy is to lockdown your opponent. Lock cards out of the game by banishing or lock an existing graveyard with Necrovalley. Final Countdown was added so we don't deck out. Inspector Boarder to control monster effects. Fossil Dyna and any 3 Barrier Statue cards listed will do but I chose 3 Torrents because no one really plays water monsters these days. Moon Mirror Shield for battle. Phantom Knights' Wing to stop effect pops. I chose Quaking because i like to deal with the cards on the field saving them for later. Judgment & Bribe to negate scary things and halt backrow plays. Feel free to swap out cards to your preference but I feel like i've optimized this deck as best i can.

Combos to be wary of:

Rai-Oh will conflict with Pot of Duality so choose according to the deck you're facing and current cards your dealing with. Honestly though, Rai-Oh's effect is more important against search decks.

Inspector boarder will not allow you to activate Yata-Garasu's effects. This does mean however you can combine it with other spirit cards like Amano to keep in on the field.

deck_excerpt: My adaptation of my going second Invoked Dogmatika Shaddoll deck, relative to the Master Duel format and ban list.
deck_description: Hi, Grayewick here, and I love Fusion summoning, as I've always stated in my guides. Here's the list of my going second Invoked Dogmatika Shaddolls, Master Duel legal. Your going first choices will be in the main and your going second options will be at the side deck. I wanna keep it as concise as possible so, let's get to it. (Edit: There might've been a small rant somewhere in there so, yeah... oops.) • "Where Maximus? modcheck" - Yeah, we're not playing Dogmatika Maximus because Drytrons are annoying as fuck and should get hit whenever a ban list comes in Master Duel. Why you wouldn't wanna do this? They play Herald of the Arc Light and Elder Entity N'tss. Also, Lyrilusc Tri-Brigades, they also have Tri-Brigade Bearbrumm the Rampant Rampager which can search upon getting sent to the GY and Tri-Brigade Ferrijit the Barren Blossom which draws, and both triggers off of Maximus' effect. That's absolutely terrible for you. That's also why I prefer Artemis, the Magistus Moon Maiden in this build instead of the usual Salamangreat Almiraj + Secure Gardna. Not only is it cheaper to build this way and leaves you one Extra Deck slot to work with, but it's one less summon for Nibiru, the Primal Being. He would be better in a format where Drytrons and Tri-Brigades are dead, which is why I haven't played Master Duel for a while and went back to the TCG for some breath of fresh air, because his main purpose is to kill your opponent's Extra Deck. This is also why we're not running Nadir Servant and Titaniklad the Ash Dragon, because sending it off Dogmatika Punishment would be too slow, and you'd much rather send either an El Shaddoll Apkallone or a Psy-Framelord Omega. • "Double Resh?" - Yes. That's standard for my builds. I disagree with playing just one of this card, and in a format where Super Polymerization is only semi-limited, there's really no reason not to run an extra copy for insurance. • x3 Cursed Seal of the Forbidden Spell - One of the most underrated Counter Traps in the game, like holy shit. You can effectively disable three different Spells for the rest of the DUEL, in a best of one format. If you're playing against Drytrons and you chain this in response to their Meteonis Drytron, that means they cannot Ritual Summon AT ALL for the rest of that duel. That's STUPID and I love it. We're playing 12 Spells to fodder this Trap, and this can also act as a Trap fodder for Invoked Mechaba for coverage. BUT if you have access to triple Solemn Judgments or Solemn Strikes, you can do it. I'll just leave this up to your preference. • x3 Evenly Matched - This is a staple for my builds so long as it's still a best of one format, especially on going second decks. This is harder to play around than Lightning Storm, which is a UR btw. This, Cursed Seal of the Forbidden Spell, and Solemn Judgment/Solemn Strike can all share slots, so it really depends on you on how many ratios of them you can or want to play. • Predaplant Dragostapelia - Thunder Dragons are (usually) a Fusion strategy, and I LOVE and respect Fusion strategies due to them being innately -1 or 2 but still keeping up with the meta game from time to time, but I too can make exceptions. Pardon my language, but I FUCKING HATE Thunder Dragon Colossus with a fervent passion comparable to that of Payne96' desire for a Pyro/Volcanic support coming into the TCG/OCG. I am not sorry for these Thunder Dragon players but Colossus should never come back to the TCG and should be banned in Master Duel as well, I'd even say that that card should have never been printed alongside Maxx "C" and I will literally fight you for it. You can argue the same thing for El Shaddoll Winda all you want, but she does not have protection like Colossus does and is frail in comparison. Also Prank-Kids, you might've noticed by now how I hate decks that gain so much advantage off of so little resources. • Mudragon of the Swamp - For Drytrons and Tri-Brigades. They both usually have cards that fits Mudragon of the Swamp's requirements. Also, there have been some EARTH Machines and rogue strategies with EARTH and WATER attributes lurking around lately, that's also why I'm playing Nehshaddoll Genius. She's an additional negate for the turn, and if you too decide to run her, you have the freedom to either choose x2 Apkallone or one of each Apkallone and El Shaddoll Shekhinaga. Also, both it and Shekhinaga gets better if you decided to use Maxx "C" instead, I only chose Droll & Lock Bird instead of it or Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring because one, Drytrons would rather be Ashed than Drolled because the latter would mean they would have to use all of the resources they have currently to make a play if they don't have an immediate answer to it, unlike Maxx "C" which can be both countered by Ash, Crossout Designator, and Called By The Grave and two, not a lot of FIRE Attributed decks are around like Infernoble Knights or Salamangreats and three, I've been hunting these Lyrilusc Tri-Brigades in the ladder like Kite Tenjo hunting Number cards. I would run three Reeshaddoll Wendi if Super Polymerization were at three as well. Some additional notes: • Match your Extra Deck with your hand traps - If you do decide to play Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring, Invoked Purgatrio would be nice to have for additional firepower since this deck has already more than enough control to it. That's also why I don't play Invoked Caliga, because there are times where I've dragged games way too long with locking my opponent down with it, El Shaddoll Winda, and Invoked Mechaba on board, but I too find myself having trouble of dealing damage. I have considered several times to play Invoked Cocytus, but he's just not worth it as of now, if you want a Super Polymerization target for WATER Attributes, El Shaddoll Anoyatyllis would be better because not only does she cut off Drytron from their gimmick, but she also stops the second part of Lyrilusc - Bird Call and in mirror matches, this turns off Resh Shaddoll Incarnation, so whoever has the more established boards usually would win. • Most decks in the ladder do not have an out to a Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax with I:P Masquerena as Link Material, with the exception of Tri-Brigade Shuraig the Ominous Omen, and some rogue strategies like Mekk-Knights because they play Lib the World Key Blademaster and some that run Kaijus but in my opinion, this is the best defensive Link 4 you can have, but if you want more firepower then look for either Accesscode Talker or Borrelsword Dragon. You can also choose to run Knightmare Unicorn or Knightmare Phoenix instead for more disruption. Overall, it's a pretty standard Invoked Dogmatika Shaddoll deck list with some personal techs. A third copy of Super Polymerization would definitely be nice but, it is what it is. It's not exactly a cheap deck to build due to Konami deciding to make the three main Shaddoll Fusion monsters all URs for some reason, but I do hope you enjoy playing this deck if you ever decide to do so.

deck_excerpt: Junk Speeder and Doppelwarrior carry you to victory.
deck_description: Hello everyone and thanks for checking out my deck.  With the release of Master Duel it brought back my love for Yu-Gi-Oh as I stopped following the game in 2014~.  This is a deck I made that got me to platinum rank in a week.  It has some negate, however prefers to go first to get your sychro monsters out.  This deck's main objective is to summon Cosmic Blazar Dragon/Shooting Star Dragon/Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon.  The best way I found was using the effects of Junk Synchron, Doppelwarrior, and Junk Speeder.  You can use Foolish Burial, One for One, Tuning (Send the top card of you deck the GY), Quickdraw Synchron, or Mathematician to send a Doppelwarrior to the GY for Junk Synchron to special summon.  From there you synchro summon Junk Speeder, into Martial Metal Marcher and Armory Arm.  Then, you can summon Cosmic Blazar Dragon.  If you have non-tuner monsters left or monster reborn I like to go for Stardust Dragon or Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon.  There are still some cards I am on the fence about having in the deck and I hope to find more impactful cards as I continue to play and experiment.  That being said here are a few cards I would switch for something else;  -Turbo Booster and Boost Warrior (I like these cards in case you are unable to get a Doppelwarrior to the GY)  -Necroid Synchro (not a great card for opener, but I find it useful to get Shooting Star Dragon out)  -Shard of Greed (two turns is too slow in today's Yu-Gi-Oh I'm learning)  -Martial Metal Marcher (Tatsunoko seems to the popular 3 star synchro tuner, I will test out to see which I prefer),  -Armory Arm ( probably better 4 star synchro monsters out there, my nostalgia for the card  keeps it in the deck for me.  Also, the extra attack it gives helps deal with decks like Blue-Eyes that have high attack monsters)  -Beelzeus of the Diabolic Dragons (I wanted a 10 star synchro in my extra deck and this seemed like the best one.  I have haven't summoned as many times as I'd like to though)  Thanks again for viewing/reading and I would appreciate it if everyone would leave there thoughts or recommendations for this deck.  I am still learning about the cards that have come out since I last play Yu-Gi-Oh and am having a lot of fun duelling again.  I hope you enjoy this deck or are able to get some ideas for your decks from it.

deck_excerpt: A spellcaster control/beatdown deck that got me Platinum in MasterDual and the cards are cute.
deck_description: The deck revolves around summoning your spellcasters to keep control of the board. Most of them have 1850ATK or 1500DEF which is specific for being able to search for them in decks and in GYs. Majority of Victories come from swinging wildly with the spellcasters or having your opponent surrender because you hindered them enough. STAPLES: -Raigeki/Lightning Storm/Veiler/AshBlossom/Terraforming/MST/Dimensional Barrier - Pretty self explanatory, feel free to add/remove as you see fit. LUNA: -A simple way of getting spellcaster cards into your hand from your deck with 1850ATK; which is all the Familiar Possessed creatures. Can also be used to disrupt your opponent by forcing them to trash a card or have cards sent back to their hands/ExtraDeck DOGMATIKA: -Ecclesia and Fluerdelis are easy summons in reaction to your opponents summoning from the extra deck, they are also Spellcasters and they are annoying to deal with. EDA: -Helpful for special summoning cards from your Deck; they come in in Facedown defense position, but during your opponents main phase you can flip them to attack. NEFARIOUS -This is a combo piece; if you have a spellcaster in the field, you can special summon this, which then you special summon Awakened Nefarious from your deck by sending both the small nefarious and spellcaster card to the GY. Once Awakened Nefarious enters the battlefield you can bring back a spellcaster monster from your GY to your field. I run only one because you do not want this in your opening hand. ICHIRIN -I use this field spell if I'm playing against another spellcaster deck, otherwise I prioritize Secret Village. AWAKENING OF THE POSSESSED -This is IMO the most important card in the deck which is why I run three. It draws you a card when you play a spellcaster. it powers up all you cards based on the different attributes in play (why I run one copy of every Familiar Possessed). With this in play, your creatures will hit like trucks and since there are many ways to get creatures in play, you can overwhelm your opponent on power alone. SPIRIT CHARMER -I always add a spellcaster to my hand and I always set an Awakening of the possessed. POSSESSED PARTNERSHIPS -This card is loaded: Summon a spellcaster from hand or GY, destroy a face-up card, and banish it to recycle a previous spell or trap and play them in face-up position. UNPOSSESSED -Protects your familiar possessed creatures, powers them up on attack, if a creature is destroyed you can special summon a new one. Very useful in this deck. THE EXTRA DECK -Pretty straight forward, used them to get a nice creature from your opponents GY that matches the attribute (there is no dark version yet) I made this deck cuz I like the archetype, but it has shocked me how well it's doing; to the point where I'm in Platinum in MasterDuel.

We're a little over three months away from the new Marincess support in Legendary Duelist: Duels from the Deep. While that's still far away the new cards have been announced for quite a while now, giving us plenty of time to deckbuild, test ratios and optimize the new era of Marincess decks. Marincess Marincesses are a link climbing deck that aims to create an unaffected boss monster. Like every link archetype it has a Link-1 that searches the Field Spell. The Field Spell - Marincess Battle Ocean - gives the boss monster a huge ATK boost (up to 2000) and makes it unaffected if summoned with Marincess Crystal Heart. Since Marincess end in a high ATK monster that's equiped with even more monsters players can be caught off guard and don't realise all they have to do is out the field spell to remove the monsters protection and ATK buff. Marincess Wave is another means to protect your monsters. It both negates an opponent's monster and makes all your monster unaffected by your opponent's card effects. If you control a Link-3 or higher Marincess it turns into a handtrap. Keep in mind Wave has to actually negate the targeted monster in order for your monster to become unaffected. They have high recursion from the GY and a very good grind game. They are weak to backrow removal and (used to) lack almost any non-generic interaction besides the (used to be) unsearchable Wave. Anemone triggers if it leaves the field so always equip it with Battle Ocean. If your monster gets removed during your opponent's turn Anemone will trigger for extra recursion. New Support I'll quickly go over some of the new, relevant cards. Marincess Sleepy Maiden: Specials Summons herself by protecting a Marincess card. Equips a Marincess Link monster from your GY to a Marincess Link monster you control. --> Extender, niche protection and helps with OTK'ing. Marincess Springirl: Banishes a "Marincess" monster from GY; Special Summons itself. Mills cards equal to the number of "Marincess" monsters if it's linked off for a WATER Link monster and has a little burn effect. --> Extender and may fill up GY with ressources. Marincess Dive: Special Summons non-Link "Marincess" monster from GY or if you control Battle Ocean Special Summons one "Marincess" monster from deck. --> Extender. Marincess Coral Triangle: Link-3 that discards a WATER; searches a "Marincess" Trap Wave. Very strong extender past your first turn. --> Archetypal Trap Searcher and Extender past first turn. Marincess Aqua Argonaut: Link-4 that targets a WATER you control and a card your opponent controls; returns them to hand (Ignition Effect). Summons a Marincess monster equipped to it; Negates Spell/Trap avtication and destroy. --> Spell/Trap negate and card removal. Old Combos These are the combo lines you can do in current Marincess decks. These lines are still good to know so I'll go over these first. 1-card combo: Marincess Blue Tang OR Marincess Sea Horse OR Cynet Mining + Card to send (to add Blue Tang)
  1. NS Blue Tang/Sea Horse. If Blue Tang, effect to mill Sea Horse
  2. Link Tang/Horse into Blue Slug
  3. Trigger CL1 Slug to add Sea Horse to hand, CL2 Tang to excavate the top three cards and add an excavated Marincess card
  4. SS Sea Horse
  5. Link into Sea Angel, effect to add Battle Ocean // activate Battle Ocean before step 8
  6. Link Slug and Angel into Splash Mage, effect to SS Tang/Horse
  7. Link both into Coral Anemone, effect to SS Splash Mage
  8. Link both into Marincess Great Bubble Reef
  9. Trigger CL1 Anemone to add back Tang, CL2 Battle Ocean to equip Links in GY // equip 2-3 Links, keep at least 2 WATER + Horse in GY
    • 4600 ATK monster that gains more ATK and draws you another card. No interaction but the drawing power allows for good use of handtraps. Access to Wave makes it unaffected
2-card combo: Marincess Blue Tang/Sea Horse + Marincess Mandarin/Pascalus/Cynet Mining/WATER extender OR 2 out of Marincess Mandarin/Pascalus/Cynet Mining
  1. NS Tang/Horse. If Tang, effect to mill Horse // or Mandarin if Horse is in hand
  2. Link Tang/Horse into Slug
  3. Trigger CL1 Slug to add Horse to hand, CL2 Tang to excavate // Order doesn't matter if you milled Mandarin. CL2 Tang baits Ash, CL2 Slug baits Belle
  4. SS Horse
  5. Link into Angel, effect to add Battle Ocean // activate Battle Ocean before step 9
  6. Summon extender
  7. Link extender and Slug into Crystal Heart
  8. Link Heart and Angel into Coral Anemone, effect to SS Crystal Heart
  9. Link both into Marincess Great Bubble Reef
    • Unaffected 46oo ATK monster that gains more ATK and draws you cards. 
New Combos 1-card combo: Marincess Blue Tang OR Marincess Sea Horse OR Cynet Mining + Card to send (to add Blue Tang) OR Marincess Mandarin + Springirl
  • For Mandarin and Springirl: NS Mandarin, link into Slug, DON'T use Slug's effect. Banish Mandaring for Springirl. Link Springirl into Sea Angel and the rest is the same
  • For any starter but Blue Tang:
    1. Same combo up to step 5
    2. Link Slug and Angel into Coral Anemone, SS any Marincess
    3. Link both into Marincess Coral Triangle
    4. Trigger CL1 Anemone to add back Tang/Horse, CL2 Battle Ocean to equip all 3 Marincess Link monsters from GY
    5. Effect Triangle to discard Tang/Horse and add Wave
      • 3500 ATK monster that becomes unaffected after negating a monster effect with Wave
  • For Blue Tang:
    1. NS Blue Tang, effect to mill Sleepy Maiden
    2. Link Tang into Blue Slug
    3. CL1 Slug targeting Maiden, CL2 Tang
    4. SS Maiden
    5. Link both into Coral Anemone, SS Tang.
    6. Link Tang into Sea Angel and add Marincess Dive
    7. Link Anemone and Angel into Coral Triangle and trigger Anemone to add back Tang or Maiden
    8. Triangle effect, discarding the added Marincess to search Wave
    9. Use Dive to SS Tang or Maiden
    10. Link Triangle and the other Marincess for Marincess Aqua Argonaut.
    11. Banish Maiden in GY to equip Argonaut with Coral Anemone
      • 2300 ATK monster with a S/T negate that becomes unaffected after negating a monster effect with Wave
2-card combo: Marincess Blue Tang/Sea Horse + Marincess Mandarin/Pascalus/Springirl/Dive/Battle Ocean/Cynet Mining/WATER extender OR 2 out of Marincess Mandarin/Springirl/Pascalus/Dive/Battle Ocean/Cynet Mining (+ card to send unless paired with Mandarin) (Springirl + Mandarin or Battle Ocean + Dive does not work)
  • For opening Battle Ocean/Dive and any of the latter combo pieces // not Tang/Horse/Cynet
    1. NS starter
    2. Link into Sea Angel right away, effect to add Battle Ocean/Dive // the one you don't have access to
    3. Activate Battle Ocean, then Dive afterwards to SS Blue Tang from deck, effect to mill Sea Horse
    4. Link both into Coral Anemone
    5. Effect Anemone to SS Tang
    6. Link off Tang into Slug
    7. Trigger CL1 Slug targetting Horse, CL2 Tang
    8. Link Slug and Anemone into Coral Triangle, trigger Anemone to add Marincess monster to hand
    9. Triangle effect, discard the previously added monster to add Wave
    10. SS Horse
    11. Link Triangle and Horse into Marincess Aqua Argonaut
    12. Trigger Battle Ocean, equipping Triangle, Anemone and another Marincess Link
      • 4300 ATK monster with Spell/Trap negate and a monster effect negate after which it becomes unaffected for the turn
  • For opening Tang/Horse and any additionally mentioned card
    1. Same 2-card combo up to step 6 // depending on the extender you might have to summon it earlier. eg Pascalus as your NS to SS Tang/Horse
    2. Link Slug and Angel into Anemone, effect to SS a Marincess from GY
    3. Link Anemone and Marincess into Triangle
    4. Trigger Anemone to add Marincess monster to hand
    5. Triangle effect, discard previously added monster to add Wave
    6. Link Triangle and extender into Marincess Aqua Argonaut
    7. Trigger Battle Ocean, equipping Triangle, Anemone and another Marincess Link
      • 4300 ATK monster with Spell/Trap negate and a monster effect negate after which it becomes unaffected for the turn
Additional Cards Marincess Basilalima offers protection before Wave is used. Good if you have enough in hand already and don't need Tang's mill. You have many extenders so there's a r4nk engine in here. With one more extender you may be able to use two level 4s to go into Bahamut Shark, summon Toadally Awesome and then use Shark as the extender for the Link-4 while also searching Wave. Marincess Crystal Heart is not as important anymore but should not be disregarded since it makes your monster unaffected during your turn, too. Marincess Marbled Rock gives extra recursion which is good to have past turn 1 to play through more interaction. Marincess Wonder Heart is a terrible card turn 1 but enables an OTK without having to use Accesscode, which would disable a lot of effect that would otherwise lock you into WATER. The Side deck is additional handtraps and Crossout targets. Since Battle Ocean is no longer a brick (you can then search Dive instead with Angel) I recommend playing 2. Before I played 1 Battle Ocean - 3 Dive but there's virtually no reason to play that over 2 -2 since opening one of them means searching the other. You could always play 2 Battle Ocean - 3 Dive. There's plenty of Level 4 extenders. Tenyi Spirit -Shthana, Silent Angler and Abyss Shark (with 1 Silent Angler). Depending on how many you play making r4nks becomes even easier. Changes to the decklist Since I last uploaded this list I added a copy of Sleepy Maiden. Now I don't think she's mandatory to include in every decklist. Her biggest downside is her level but what she does she does pretty well. Ideally you end with Aqua Argonaut in your EMZ so once you're going for the OTK you would have to waste a lot of resources setting up a Marincess Wonder Heart in your EMZ to have her equipped with Mariness Link monsters. Milling Maiden off of Blue Tang allows your Wonder Heart in the MMZ to be equipped with a Marincess Link monster, making it easier to OTK through monsters. Her extension is also pretty great, considering the protection persists (or should, haven't checked out any rulings yet) even if she leaves the field. Since she can protect any Marincess card she can permanently protect your Field Spell from destruction, which is absolutely insane. Outing the Field Spell is how you out this deck, once the Field Spell gains protection you're in a fantastic spot. All you gotta do now is negate non-destructive effects that could out your Field Spell and you're good to go. I also updated some handtraps but obviously handtraps will adapt to the meta so at the end of the day they can be whatever. If you're not on Crossout you could get away with running less handtraps and either play more extenders or some backrow removal if you want.
Draft Deck V1

That's right, Brick-Eyes White Dragon is back. Consistency? Who needs that? This is the deck I love to run in Master Duel which took me to plat tier 5. Where's Maxx "C"? Where's the hand traps? Don't need them. I don't bow down to the meta. Now, there are cards that you can replace for the meta, but you need to figure out which ones so you can adjust it to your play style. Now go out there and have fun!

It doesn't bode very well against Anti-Spell Decks, but I suppose that should be expected in any Sky Striker Deck. Fusion Destiny is now Semi-Limited, I did have it at three copies     MAIN DECK - 40  Monsters: 15  x2 Strategic Striker - HAMP  x1 Destiny HERO - Dasher  x1 Destiny HERO - Celestial  x3 Sky Striker Ace - Raye  x2 Sky Striker Ace - Roze  x3 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring  x3 Effect Veiler     Spells: 20  x1 Called by the Grave  x2 Fusion Destiny  x1 Harpie's Feather Duster  x1 Reinforcement of the Army  x2 Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero  x2 Sky Striker Maneuver - Afterburners!  x1 Sky Striker Maneuver - Jamming Waves!  x1 Sky Striker Mecha - Hornet Drones  x2 Sky Striker Mecha - Shark Cannon  x3 Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor  x1 Sky Striker Mecha Modules - Multirole  x1 Sky Striker Mecharmory - Hercules Base  x1 Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage!  x1 Terraforming     Traps: 5  x2 Dimension Wall  x3 Infinite Impermanence        EXTRA DECK - 15  Fusion: 1  x1 Destiny HERO - Destroyer Phoenix Enforcer     Link: 14  x1 Predaplant Verte Anaconda  x1 Accesscode Talker  x1 Selene, Queen of the Master Magicians  x1 Crystron Halqifibrax  x1 Sky Striker Ace - Zeke  x1 Sky Striker Ace - Kaina  x2 Sky Striker Ace - Hayate  x3 Sky Striker Ace - Kagari  x3 Sky Striker Ace Shizuku        SIDE DECK - 15  Main: 13  x3 Nibiru, the Primal Being  x1 Dinowrestler Pankratops  x2 Limiter Removal  x1 Monster Reborn  x1 Mystic Mine  x2 Mystical Space Typhoon  x2 Sky Striker Mobilize - Linkage!  x1 Raigeki     Extra: 2  x1 Ningirsu the World Chalice Warrior  x1 Artemis, the Magistus Moon Maiden        I have tried There can be Only One. But upon learning that it doesn't let you Link away your Sky Striker monster for another, I replaced it with Dimension Wall.     Basic Combos:  Going First - Try opening with Shizuku. This will let you search a Sky Striker Spell at the end of the turn.  Going Second - Open with Hayate and attack directly, then send whatever Sky Striker card you want to your GY (Recommend Widow Anchor, but situations vary). Then Link away into Kagari to retrieve the Sky Striker Spell you need from your GY. Finish with Linking into Shizuku for that extra Search.  Monster Destroyed - Get back Raye and Quick Effect her into Kaina to prevent you opponent's most dangerous Monster from attacking.  Finisher - When you have your opponent at 5300 LP or less, start the Talker Combo with Halqifibrax and Selene. You should have enough different Attribute Link Monsters in your GY to wipe your opponent's whole field of Monsters

deck_excerpt: Wait, what's that? An archetype that does not use a Normal Summon, and is consisted of LIGHT Attributed monsters???
deck_description: Hey wassup, it’s me, Grayewick the Fusion strategy enjoyer back with uh… another smokescreen strategy. I mean, it still features Invoked so it’s technically still half a Fusion strategy but anyway, presenting Invoked Galaxy-Eyes.  “So, why play this jank?” Galaxy-Eyes, apart from Galaxy Soldier and Galaxy Wizard, does not play any relevant Normal Summon so, you know… I mean, at this point Konami should really consider giving every strategy a dedicated Normal Summon at this point else, people like me are just gonna keep splashing Invoked into it. I mean, that won't stop us but, you know what I mean. “What makes this playable or “good” enough?” Depending on how good your hand is, this deck can bring out any combinations of either Number 90: Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord, Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy, Cyber Dragon Infinity, and/or Invoked Mechaba, all before 5 summons, playing around Nibiru the Primal Being. “How do you win?” Controlling your opponent’s Monster and Spell effects, and Mechaba being technically an omni-negator. Also as per usual, we’re running traps which are three copies of Tachyon Transmigration. This card is funky and is one of the nuttiest Counter Trap cards I've read in my whole life and I love it. If your opponent becomes way too greedy at their chain links, just flip this up while you control any “Galaxy-Eyes” monster, and it negates all cards activated in that chain prior to it and shuffles them all away into the Deck, and this being a Counter Trap means that the only way your opponent could stop this is specifically with another Counter Trap, mainly Solemn Judgment. Your main source of firepower will be from your Galaxy-Eyes monsters, being Galaxy-Eyes Cipher X Dragon, Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Blade Dragon, Galaxy-Eyes Full Armor Photon Dragon, and Invoked Purgatrio. We’re not running Neo Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon in the deck because the space is too tight for one more room, but due to the prevalence of Zoodiacs, Lyrilusc, Divine Arsenal AA-Zeus – Sky Thunder, and Number F0: Utopic Draco Future, I’m heavily considering it. Overall, despite having control tools, this deck doesn’t have a problem OTK-ing and getting over big boss monsters with strong protection effects like Blue-Eyes Chaos MAX Dragon because of Number 62: Galaxy-Eyes Prime Photon Dragon. You can substitute your three Ash Blossom & Joyous Springs for any staple card you need, like three copies of Evenly Matched or Photon Stream of Destruction for going 2nd or Dimensional Barrier or Solemn Judgment for going 1st  in addition to your Tachyon Transmigrations. Since I’m already at this point, I might as well make a pure build of Galaxy-Eyes later, and that should be fun since I actually built a Galaxy-Eyes deck first when I was in high school before Blue-Eyes despite the latter being more iconic, but yeah. Invoked Galaxy-Eyes, I don’t recommend building it right away as your first deck, but if you already have both the Invoked and Galaxy-Eyes cores, here you go.

deck_name: Master Duel - The Banlist Isn't Great
deck_excerpt: Man... It's almost like they didn't balance for a best of ones format in the least.
deck_description: This is an infinite negate tri-brigade lunalight build for master duel. If you don't know how this works, basically if you can summon the simorgh link and union carrier, you can equip simorgh with mist valley thunderbird and summon apex avian off of simorgh. avian is a non OPT omni negate that requires you to bounce a card and thunderbird summons itself when bound back to the hand (no hard OPT) so basically your opponent can't do anything. The board also ends on CDI for good measure as a backup in case your opponent has something to chain to the combo.  But most of you already knew all that, time for what I'm really here for... to complain about the banlist decisions that made this deck possible.  First off, why in the fresh hell in union carrier legal, this card is so unbelievably broken because not only is this bullshit legal, but so is the buster lock. WHO THE HELL THOUGHT THIS WAS A GOOD IDEA IN A FORMAT OF BEST OF ONES!  Secondly, the simorgh link was just recently banned in the TCG, this card is so broken be it fetching an omni negate or a barrier statue and this is without union carrier.  Thirdly is that Maxx "c" is legal in this format... I don't think this card is healthy for a best of one format, activating it wins you the game, and if your opponent doesn't have games 2 and 3 to try to make a comeback it is incredibly unfair.  last is that there are quite a few floodgates that should never be legal that are in this format, not playing them here because I respect my dignity and opponents, but again triple skill drain alongside emptiness being legal is yet again... not okay for a format of best of ones.

deck_excerpt: The best Drytron variant post banlist February 2022
deck_description:
After the banlist, Drytron suffered quite a hit with Eva being banned. As a result, The herald variant is now unplayable due to consistency issues following the Eva ban. Most Drytron pro players will return to this Drytron strategy that I will be showing you today. Big thank to Youtuber Tatsym for uploading the decklist in March 2021 as it inspired me a lot to build this deck and play it competitively. Strengths:
  • Nibiru-proof by means of Vendread Battlelord, a card that allows you to prohibit a card type( monster, spell or trap from activating)Be mindful that this card should. be prioritized to summon before the 5th summon by using the Vendread ritual spell Revendread Evolution.
  • Great consistency, due to multiple search cards and much more drytron than other variants, this deck is pretty consistent
  • Huge endboard: The endboard is really absurd if you can full combo. For example, with drytron Nova+any card that leads to Battlelord is Phul( quick ritual. summon to go into Bethor for a pop 4 or 5 potentially), I:P for apollousa or Underworld Goddess according to your matchup, Abyss Dweller and Lancea with followup from typically 3 to 4 drytrons in your GY.                                                                                                                                                                                                            Weakness:
  • Lose to Droll: Not too different from the Herald variant, thís deck loses to Droll really hard. However, I chose to play 3 Gamma for this issue and as people don't usually main deck droll anymore for the fallen of the old Drytron and Bird-ups. If they side Droll against you, you can have crossout designator instead of the appointer of the Red Lotus in the side deck to cover more handtraps and shut down going second cards such as Droplet and Dark ruler no more.
  • Hard time going second: If you don't open with great going second cards, you better be ready to go for Zeus. One typical play that i usually use is to Xyz summon Mu-beta Fafnir with no eff and then Downerd straight to Zeus.                                                                                                                                                                                          Combos There are many hands that you can combo with but the main goal is to get Battlelord out ASAP and get to curious. I would say 90% of the hands that lead to Curious can help you full combo.

deck_excerpt: Basically your usual Halqifibrax Combo with Extra Steps (1 card combo = Borrelboi + Arc Light end board)
deck_description:
Note: Silverroket Dragon can be replaced with ANY non-Tuner Lvl 4 Rokket monster Introductions So what is Halqifibrax Combo? Basically you Normal Summon a Tuner that can revive itself (Jet Synchron, Glow-up Bulb, Plaguespreader Zombie, etc), or a monster that can Special Summon a Tuner from the Deck, and you end with 3 counters Borreload Savage Dragon  + Herald of the Arc Light without a single Extender (if not interrupted) The Combo is as follows:
  1. Normal Summon Jet Synchron/Plaguespreader
  2. Link into Almiraj -> Revive Jet Synchron/Plaguespreader
  3. Link into Crystron Halqifibrax -> Summon Deskbot 001
  4. Link into Mecha Phantom Beast Auroradon -> Summon 3 Lvl 3 Tokens -> Trigger Deskbot 001 to revive from GY
  5. Synchro 1 Token + Deskbot 001 into Herald of the Arc Light
  6. Auroradon Tribute itself and 1 Token to Summon Mecha Phantom Beast O-Lion from the Deck
  7. Synchro O-Lion + 1 Token into a Lvl 5 Synchro Tuner -> Trigger O-Lion to Summon a Lvl 3 Token
  8. Synchro those 2 into Borreload Savage Dragon -> Equip Auroradon
  9. Enjoy your free 2 Omni-Negates
Extra Combos Just by putting a single Synchro and a single Garnet in your Deck, you can get an extra Omni-Negate Counter Trap with the exact same resources. What is that Synchro? Denglong, the First of the Yang Zing, a currently banned card in the TCG The Extra Combo is as follows:
  1. Same Combo as 1-5, the lvl 5 Synchro Tuner is Denglong -> Denglong add Nine Pillars of the Yang Zing
  2. Synchro into Borreload Savage Dragon -> Equip Auroradon -> Denglong Trigger to Summon a Yang Zing (preferably Chi Wen) from the Deck
  3. Enjoy your FREE Omni-Negate that can negate Dark Ruler, and potentially Droplet
Extenders Does the Combo ends there? NOPE, that's just 1 card combo. What if you have an extra Extender in your hand? The best Extender I could think of is Quick-Lauch. Why Quick Launch? Because Quick Launch can Special Summon Rokket Tracer, and guess what Tracer can do? Pop a Yang Zing to Summon a Lvl 4 Rokket from the Deck. In this case, the Yang Zing doesn't miss timing because Tracer says and if you do. This will allow you to make another Lvl 8 Synchro without losing advantage. But keep in mind that Tracer locks you into DARK Extra Deck monsters only, which mean you can't make Dragite from this. If you want to make Dragite, you have to make it early in place of Borreload. Then you can make Borreload later with Tracer The other good Extender is Nemesis Corridor. Since Jet Synchron/Plaguespreader is inevitably going to get banished by its own effect. Corridor is pretty much a free Thunder Dragon Colossus The last Extenders are Destrudo and Instant Fusion. These 2 doesn't extend the Combo itself (Same Combo as having no Extender), instead they support the Combo consistency. If your Jet Synchron/Plaguespreader Searcher got negated, just use Destrudo/Instant Fusion and you will still Full Combo (if they have no more interruptions) Things You Should Know
  • You can Summon Jet Synchron/Plaguespreader off Halqifibrax to go into Unicorn into Accesscode instead (Going second)
  • Most of the Link Monsters are used for Turn 2 or higher
  • FA Dawn Dragster and Yazi, Evil of the Yang Zing can easily be Summoned from Destrudo
  • You can make 3 Materials Apollousa with 2 Extenders if your Halqifibrax got Negated
  • If your Halqifibrax got Negated, you can still end with Borreload via Quick Launch (Tracer pop Halqifibrax -> Synchro into Borreload)
  • If you open up Destrudo, Prioritize Normal Summoning your Searcher over the Tuners themself to bait out handtraps
  • If Halqifibrax got negated, you can banish it during your opponent's turn to go into Denglong to maybe survive the turn, then you can shuffle back Halqifibrax with Corridor
  • Pot of Avarice is used to reset your Extra Deck and Combo Pieces so that you can do the Halqifibrax Combo again next turn
  • Yazi can pop 1 card and itself, which then float into Mare Mare; generating 3 free tokens that can be used for Link plays (Phoenix -> Unicorn -> Halqifibrax/Accesscode)
Summary Is the Deck good? The main problem with the Deck is the little amount of Extender it has, which mean it usually lose to handtraps. A single Ash Blossom can cost you the game. However, if you successfully do the Combo, you pretty much win the game (most of the time). Without Side Deck, you don't have to worry about things like Kaiju or Sphere Mode as much. This board can easily be broken by a single Droplet (sending monsters and Traps), but you still have Nine Pillars The other Weakness that the Deck has is Garnets. If you draw Tracer, your Quick Launch is less effective. If you draw O-Lion, can't make Borreload. This issue could be solved by Plaguespreader returning a card back into the Deck How about consistency? I decided to play a 48 cards Deck because I need some board breaker going 2nd. You may think that it's not consistent because of it, but remember that you have 20 Starters (6 is Destrudo, 1 is Instant Fusion) that leads you into the Combo. That literally means you have more than 90% chance to open at least 1 Starter (80% if you don't count Destrudo and Instant Fusion). So I would say it's pretty consistent (I tried using 5 sample draws and I got at least 1 Starter 10x in a row). Also more Cards mean less chance to draw Garnets Is the Deck Expensive? Well... It's very Expensive actually. 9N, 7R, 24 SR, 23 UR (Remember that one of the SR is easily replaceable, check Note). But don't worry, the Staples are replaceable, Extra Deck cards that aren't mentioned in the Combo are replaceable... Good Luck getting those SR/UR CPs!!! Update Added Cards: 1x Mare Mare, 3x Forbidden Droplets, 3x Dragon Shrine Replaced Cards: 2x Ash Blossoms -> 3x Infinite Impermanence (Trading Maxx "C" counter for better board breaker + better synergy with Droplet) Updated text about consistency and added list on "Things You Should Know"

deck_excerpt: Maxx "C", and you left me with an Attack Position monster, it'd be a shame if you won't have another turn to play Yu-Gi-Oh.
deck_description: Hi, Grayewick the Fusion strategy enjoyer here, back with an EDOPro AI classic, Mathmechs. Yes, I blind second. Yes, this isn't a cheap deck to build. Yes, I do not play Pot of Desires because everyone's playing Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring. Yes, I literally do not care about getting Maxx "C"-ed because your opponent won't have another turn to play as soon as either Avramax or Final Sigma hits the board. As per usual, cards on the main are the cards that I would personally play and the tech options will be placed in the side. "So, how does this deck exactly work?" In summation: One Punch. First of all, let me address this one thing: If not for literally Parallel eXceed and even with Mathmech Diameter honestly, this deck would be slow as fuck. I'd be running Double Summons like I'm playing a slower version of Powerload Ogre turbo and yes, it does brick, that's why we blind second to get that extra card, and you'll never know if your opponent is playing a blind second strategy as well, and if they do, they probably run Kaijus, which kills all your boss monsters. So deck strategy, it's pretty straightforward. Make either Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax, Accesscode Talker, Borrelsword Dragon, or the archetypal boss monster Geomathmech Final Sigma and one shot your opponent with big number. That's why we also run Forbidden Droplet and Evenly Matched, because we want to end games as soon as possible, and it would be stupid for your opponent to leave a back row without a monster on the field, unless it's an Eldlich player that hard drew Skill Drain. So yeah, if you want to be extra annoying, use Skill Drain as well after summoning Geomathmech Final Sigma and trigger your opponent's PTSD from Apoqliphort Towers turbo because fuck it, it's basically the same thing, except Towers messes up with your opponent's resources and makes them feel violated while Final Sigma messes up with your opponent's LP and pride after getting one shot by a deck that's not even rogue. Have fun in the ladder.

deck_excerpt: Drytron is alive, Herald is dead. Lesgo?
deck_description:
Now Drytron don't have a way to make "unbreakable" boards ;-; So since we can't win in one combo now, i made this deck aimed for a better grind game and this board: Drytron Meteonis Draconids - Red-eyes Dark Dragoon - Masquerena - Predaplant Verte Anaconda.  
  • Explaining the engines:
  1. From my short experience using this megalith engine (1xMegalith Phul, 1xMegalith Bethor and a second Meteonis Drytron) i don't like it, but it's not like it is bad. Is Difficult to explain how im feeling. Anyway it adds another tool for the deck and can be replaced if you found something better.
  2. The Cyber Angel engine is strong as always and can be used to search Vanity's Ruler that is a insta win against many decks and helps playing against nibiru.
  3. Dragoon: Dragoon: Sussy.
 
  • Some ideas:
At OCG there's some drytron decks using this Scythe-lock strategy with Halqifibrax and Artifact Dagda: you search Artifact Scythe either with Cyber Angel Benten or Dagda then link summon Halqifibrax, at the opponent turn you summon T .G. Wonder Magician with Halqifibrax effect and destroy Scythe, Scythe will trigger, special summoning itself while locking your opponent extra deck and then you activate Wonder Magician Quick effect and synchro summon Baronne de Fleur. Its a good combo but since i am already using Vanity's Ruler i think it isn't necessary in this deck. Other thing that i want to note is that Nibiru will destroy Drytron like a Meteor now that is difficult to make a early negate or use Herald of Orange Light (tbh you can use Orange Light but it isn't good without eva, maybe 1 copie at maximum since you can search it). Droll is also problematic for the same reason. I might start using 2-3 Crossout Designator and one Orange Light for that reason.   I hope you have a good day my fellow Drytron enjoyner. And please correct me if did said something wrong, im still learning after all.     GLHF

deck_excerpt: Danger Dark World for the win
deck_description: Here is my Danger Dark World Deck list I hope you like it

Hi, Grayewick here, and I'm not gonna waste more time because this is basically just the most F2P version of the most F2P beat down deck you could ever build, Mathmechs. This is basically just Final Sigma turbo. The slots for Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring, Forbidden Droplet, Evenly Matched, and Skill Drain can pretty much be any staple cards you want, but if you do have Cynet Mining or Pot of Desires, use them for consistency. I only use Forbidden Droplet instead of Forbidden Chalice or Infinite Impermanence because this is a F2P build and I can use it in either Battle or Damage Step to pitch my Mathmechs from my hand to the GY and it's the easiest UR to farm. Your usual combo line would be: • Foolish Burial, Forbidden Droplet, or Cynet Mining, pitching Multiplication to add Diameter • Normal Summon Diameter to Special Summon said Multiplication • Either Special Summon Addition or Subtraction from the hand • Make Final Sigma and trigger Multiplication in the graveyard, targeting Final Sigma, then attack. Just make sure not to summon Final Sigma while Skill Drain was up, instead activate Skill Drain when Final Sigma is already face-up on the field. So yeah, actual short guide this time. This is not a competitive form by any means, instead just a cheap yet playable version of it.
